    "With this collisional term, the transport equation can be solved analytically [222].In nucleus-nucleus collisions, the quarkonium initial distribution is treated as a superposition of quarkonium distribution in pp collisions.",
    "Cold-nuclear-matter effects, such as nuclear absorption, Cronin effect, and shadowing effect, are included by modifying the initial distribution extracted from pp collisions.",
    "For the non-prompt J/ψ from B decays, the Langevin equation is employed to simulate the energy loss of bottom quarks in the medium [223].",
    "The hadronization of bottom quarks into B mesons is described with the instantaneous coalescence model [223].",
    "Model ingredients• In-medium potential Charmonia and bottomonia experience a color screening effect in the hot deconfined medium, which reduces the heavy-quark potential and the in-medium binding energies."
